import GQ2.GammaA
import GQ2.MaxProP

/-!
# The universal marking is admissible in the limit  (ticket P-04)

`őď_A = F‚āĄ ‚ßł N_A` (paper ¬ß2.1, eq. (7); `GQ2/GammaA.lean`) is the largest quotient of the free
profinite group `F‚āĄ` all of whose finite quotients are admissible.  This file proves that the
presentation data survives the limit ‚ÄĒ the three facts Prop 2.3 (P-05) needs about `őď_A` itself:

* **relators die in the limit**: `tameRelator_mem_NA` / `wildRelator_mem_NA` ‚ÄĒ the profinite
  relator words of the universal marking (relations (5)/(6)) lie in `N_A`, i.e. their images in
  `őď_A` are `1` (`quotientMk_tameRelator_eq_one` / `quotientMk_wildRelator_eq_one`);
* **the admissible opens are exactly the opens above `N_A`** (`isAdmissibleU_iff_NA_le`) ‚ÄĒ the
  order-theoretic form of "`őď_A`'s finite quotients are the admissible quotients";
* **the wild pair's closed normal closure is pro-2 in the limit** (`isProP_wildCore`): the closed
  normal subgroup `‚ü®‚ü®x‚āÄ, x‚āĀ‚ü©‚ü© ‚Č§ őď_A` generated by the images of `x‚āÄ, x‚āĀ` is a pro-2 group ‚ÄĒ the
  pro-2 condition of eq. (7) holds for `őď_A` itself, not just for its finite quotients.

## Design note: the limit argument

The engine is the **directedness of the admissible family** (the subdirect-closure content of
paper Lemma 2.1, `GQ2/Subdirect.lean`), run through the same compactness pattern as
`GQ2/MaxProP.lean`:

1. `isAdmissibleU_top`: the trivial quotient is admissible (all four conditions are trivial in a
   subsingleton), so the admissible family is nonempty ‚ÄĒ no appeal to the Appendix-B `S‚āÉ`
   quotient is needed.
2. `isAdmissibleU_inf`: admissibility is closed under `U ‚äď V`.  Generation holds in *every*
   finite quotient of `F‚āĄ` (`generates_univMarking_map` ‚ÄĒ density of the abstract free group in
   its profinite completion); the relators die in `U ‚äď V` because they die in `U` and in `V`
   (this is where `tameRelator_mem_of_isAdmissibleU` recurs); and the 2-core condition passes to
   `U ‚äď V` **subdirectly**: an element of the normal closure in `F‚āĄ ‚ßł U ‚äď V` has a lift whose
   images in `F‚āĄ ‚ßł U` and `F‚āĄ ‚ßł V` are 2-elements, so it is a 2-element
   (`isPGroup_normalClosure_image_inf`, the elementwise form of "`Q_A` is closed under subdirect
   products", Lemma 2.1).
3. `exists_isAdmissibleU_le`: **admissible domination** ‚ÄĒ every open normal `W ‚Č• N_A` contains an
   admissible `U`.  Compactness: the family `{U ‚ą© WŠ∂ú}` over admissible `U` is a directed (by 2)
   family of closed sets in the compact `F‚āĄ`; were all nonempty, their intersection would meet
   `N_A ‚ą© WŠ∂ú = ‚ąÖ`.  (Same pattern as `isPGroup_quotient_of_proPKernel_le`.)
4. `isAdmissibleU_of_NA_le`: push admissibility from the dominating `U` up to `W` along
   `F‚āĄ ‚ßł U ‚Ü† F‚āĄ ‚ßł W` via Lemma 2.2 (`Marking.map_admissible`).  With the trivial converse
   (`N_A` is an intersection) this gives the characterization `isAdmissibleU_iff_NA_le`.
5. `isProP_wildCore`: for an open normal `V ‚Č§ ‚ü®‚ü®x‚āÄ,x‚āĀ‚ü©‚ü©` (subspace topology), pick an open
   normal `W ‚Č§ őď_A` with `W ‚ą© ‚ü®‚ü®x‚āÄ,x‚āĀ‚ü©‚ü© ‚Č§ V` (Krull-style: `V` is a neighbourhood of `1`);
   pull `W` back to an open normal `Ňī ‚Č• N_A` of `F‚āĄ`, which is **admissible** by 4, so the
   normal closure of `x‚āÄ, x‚āĀ` in `F‚āĄ ‚ßł Ňī` is a 2-group; a dense-image argument (the image of
   `‚ü®‚ü®x‚āÄ,x‚āĀ‚ü©‚ü© = closure M` in the *finite discrete* `őď_A ‚ßł W` equals the image of the abstract
   normal closure `M`) then bounds every element of `‚ü®‚ü®x‚āÄ,x‚āĀ‚ü©‚ü© ‚ßł V` by a 2-power.

Everything is deduced from the *definition* of `N_A` ‚ÄĒ no appeal to `őď_A ‚ČÖ lim` machinery, and
no new axioms (`#print axioms` = the standard three throughout).
-/

open CategoryTheory ProfiniteGrp

namespace GQ2

/-! ## Generation in every finite quotient

The four generators topologically generate `F‚āĄ` (density of the abstract free group in its
profinite completion), so their images generate every finite (discrete) quotient.  This is the
`Generates` clause of admissibility, for free, for *every* open normal subgroup. -/

section Generation

/-- The set underlying the universal marking is the range of the generator inclusion. -/
private lemma range_of_eq_univMarking_set :
    Set.range (FreeProfiniteGroup.of : Fin 4 ‚Üí FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4))
      = {univMarking.ŌÉ, univMarking.ŌĄ, univMarking.x‚āÄ, univMarking.x‚āĀ} := by
  ext y
  simp only [Set.mem_range, univMarking, Set.mem_insert_iff, Set.mem_singleton_iff]
  constructor
  ¬∑ rintro ‚ü®i, rfl‚ü©
    fin_cases i <;> tauto
  ¬∑ rintro (rfl | rfl | rfl | rfl)
    exacts [‚ü®0, rfl‚ü©, ‚ü®1, rfl‚ü©, ‚ü®2, rfl‚ü©, ‚ü®3, rfl‚ü©]

/-- The subgroup generated by the universal marking is the (dense) image of the abstract free
group `FreeGroup (Fin 4)` in its profinite completion. -/
lemma closure_univMarking_eq_range_eta :
    Subgroup.closure ({univMarking.ŌÉ, univMarking.ŌĄ, univMarking.x‚āÄ, univMarking.x‚āĀ} :
        Set (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4)))
      = ((ProfiniteCompletion.eta (GrpCat.of (FreeGroup (Fin 4)))).hom).range := by
  rw [‚Üź range_of_eq_univMarking_set, MonoidHom.range_eq_map,
    ‚Üź FreeGroup.closure_range_of (Fin 4), MonoidHom.map_closure, ‚Üź Set.range_comp]
  rfl

/-- **Generation is automatic**: the pushed universal marking generates every finite quotient
`F‚āĄ ‚ßł W` (`W` open normal).  Density of the free group in its completion + discreteness of the
quotient. -/
theorem generates_univMarking_map (W : OpenNormalSubgroup (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4))) :
    (univMarking.map (QuotientGroup.mk' W.toSubgroup)).Generates := by
  rw [Marking.Generates]
  have himg : ({(univMarking.map (QuotientGroup.mk' W.toSubgroup)).ŌÉ,
      (univMarking.map (QuotientGroup.mk' W.toSubgroup)).ŌĄ,
      (univMarking.map (QuotientGroup.mk' W.toSubgroup)).x‚āÄ,
      (univMarking.map (QuotientGroup.mk' W.toSubgroup)).x‚āĀ} :
        Set (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4) ‚ßł W.toSubgroup))
      = (QuotientGroup.mk' W.toSubgroup) ''
          {univMarking.ŌÉ, univMarking.ŌĄ, univMarking.x‚āÄ, univMarking.x‚āĀ} := by
    simp [Marking.map, Set.image_insert_eq, Set.image_singleton]
  rw [himg, ‚Üź MonoidHom.map_closure, closure_univMarking_eq_range_eta, Subgroup.eq_top_iff']
  intro x
  obtain ‚ü®g, rfl‚ü© := QuotientGroup.mk'_surjective W.toSubgroup x
  -- `g` lies in the closure of the dense image of the free group ‚Ä¶
  have hg : g
      ‚ąą closure (Set.range (ProfiniteCompletion.etaFn (GrpCat.of (FreeGroup (Fin 4))))) := by
    rw [(ProfiniteCompletion.denseRange _).closure_eq]
    trivial
  -- ‚Ä¶ so its class lies in the image of that image (the quotient is discrete).
  have himgcl : (QuotientGroup.mk' W.toSubgroup) g
      ‚ąą closure ((QuotientGroup.mk' W.toSubgroup) ''
          Set.range (ProfiniteCompletion.etaFn (GrpCat.of (FreeGroup (Fin 4))))) :=
    image_closure_subset_closure_image QuotientGroup.continuous_mk ‚ü®g, hg, rfl‚ü©
  rw [closure_discrete] at himgcl
  obtain ‚ü®y, ‚ü®z, rfl‚ü©, hyx‚ü© := himgcl
  exact Subgroup.mem_map.mpr ‚ü®_, ‚ü®z, rfl‚ü©, hyx‚ü©

end Generation

/-! ## The relator words lie in `N_A`  (deliverable (i))

Each admissible open normal `U` kills both relator words (the finite-level relations of
`IsAdmissibleU` read back through the profinite‚üļfinite bridges of `GQ2/GammaA.lean`), so the
words lie in the intersection `N_A` ‚ÄĒ i.e. relations (5) and (6) *hold in `őď_A`*. -/

section Relators

/-- An admissible open normal subgroup contains the tame relator word (relation (5)). -/
theorem tameRelator_mem_of_isAdmissibleU {U : OpenNormalSubgroup (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4))}
    (hU : IsAdmissibleU U) : univMarking.tameRelator ‚ąą U.toSubgroup :=
  (QuotientGroup.eq_one_iff _).mp
    ((Marking.map_tameRelator_eq_one_iff (quotientMk U.toSubgroup) univMarking).mpr hU.2.1)

/-- An admissible open normal subgroup contains the wild relator word (relation (6)). -/
theorem wildRelator_mem_of_isAdmissibleU {U : OpenNormalSubgroup (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4))}
    (hU : IsAdmissibleU U) : univMarking.wildRelator ‚ąą U.toSubgroup :=
  (QuotientGroup.eq_one_iff _).mp
    ((Marking.map_wildRelator_eq_one_iff (quotientMk U.toSubgroup) univMarking).mpr hU.2.2.1)

/-- **The tame relator word lies in `N_A`** ‚ÄĒ relation (5) holds in `őď_A` (paper eq. (7)). -/
theorem tameRelator_mem_NA : univMarking.tameRelator ‚ąą NA := by
  rw [NA, Subgroup.mem_iInf]
  exact fun U => tameRelator_mem_of_isAdmissibleU U.2

/-- **The wild relator word lies in `N_A`** ‚ÄĒ relation (6) holds in `őď_A` (paper eq. (7)). -/
theorem wildRelator_mem_NA : univMarking.wildRelator ‚ąą NA := by
  rw [NA, Subgroup.mem_iInf]
  exact fun U => wildRelator_mem_of_isAdmissibleU U.2

/-- Relation (5) in `őď_A`: the image of the tame relator word is trivial. -/
@[simp] theorem quotientMk_tameRelator_eq_one :
    quotientMk NA univMarking.tameRelator = 1 :=
  (quotientMk_eq_one_iff NA).mpr tameRelator_mem_NA

/-- Relation (6) in `őď_A`: the image of the wild relator word is trivial. -/
@[simp] theorem quotientMk_wildRelator_eq_one :
    quotientMk NA univMarking.wildRelator = 1 :=
  (quotientMk_eq_one_iff NA).mpr wildRelator_mem_NA

end Relators

/-! ## Directedness of the admissible family  (Lemma 2.1 in the limit)

The admissible open normal subgroups form a *directed* family: the trivial quotient is
admissible, and admissibility is closed under `‚äď` (the subdirect-closure content of paper
Lemma 2.1: `F‚āĄ ‚ßł U ‚äď V` is a subdirect product of `F‚āĄ ‚ßł U` and `F‚āĄ ‚ßł V`).  Compactness then
gives **admissible domination**: every open normal subgroup above `N_A` contains an admissible
one, hence is itself admissible (Lemma 2.2 pushforward) ‚ÄĒ the admissible opens are *exactly*
the opens above `N_A`. -/

section Directed

/-- **Subdirect 2-core (Lemma 2.1, elementwise).**  If the normal closures of the image of `S`
in `G ‚ßł A` and in `G ‚ßł B` are `p`-groups, so is the normal closure of the image of `S` in
`G ‚ßł (A ‚äď B)`: any element lifts to `n` in the abstract normal closure of `S`, and
`n ^ p^i ‚ąą A`, `n ^ p^j ‚ąą B` give `n ^ p^(i+j) ‚ąą A ‚äď B`. -/
theorem isPGroup_normalClosure_image_inf {G : Type*} [Group G] {p : ‚Ąē} (S : Set G)
    (A B : Subgroup G) [A.Normal] [B.Normal]
    (hA : IsPGroup p (Subgroup.normalClosure ((QuotientGroup.mk' A) '' S)))
    (hB : IsPGroup p (Subgroup.normalClosure ((QuotientGroup.mk' B) '' S))) :
    IsPGroup p (Subgroup.normalClosure ((QuotientGroup.mk' (A ‚äď B)) '' S)) := by
  intro x
  -- lift `x` into the abstract normal closure of `S`
  have hx : (x : G ‚ßł (A ‚äď B))
      ‚ąą Subgroup.map (QuotientGroup.mk' (A ‚äď B)) (Subgroup.normalClosure S) := by
    rw [Subgroup.map_normalClosure _ _ (QuotientGroup.mk'_surjective _)]
    exact x.2
  obtain ‚ü®n, hn, hnx‚ü© := hx
  -- its images in the two factors are `p`-elements
  have hnA : (QuotientGroup.mk' A) n ‚ąą Subgroup.normalClosure ((QuotientGroup.mk' A) '' S) := by
    rw [‚Üź Subgroup.map_normalClosure _ _ (QuotientGroup.mk'_surjective _)]
    exact ‚ü®n, hn, rfl‚ü©
  have hnB : (QuotientGroup.mk' B) n ‚ąą Subgroup.normalClosure ((QuotientGroup.mk' B) '' S) := by
    rw [‚Üź Subgroup.map_normalClosure _ _ (QuotientGroup.mk'_surjective _)]
    exact ‚ü®n, hn, rfl‚ü©
  obtain ‚ü®i, hi‚ü© := hA ‚ü®_, hnA‚ü©
  obtain ‚ü®j, hj‚ü© := hB ‚ü®_, hnB‚ü©
  have hiA : n ^ p ^ i ‚ąą A := by
    have h := congrArg Subtype.val hi
    rw [SubgroupClass.coe_pow, OneMemClass.coe_one, ‚Üź map_pow] at h
    exact (QuotientGroup.eq_one_iff _).mp h
  have hjB : n ^ p ^ j ‚ąą B := by
    have h := congrArg Subtype.val hj
    rw [SubgroupClass.coe_pow, OneMemClass.coe_one, ‚Üź map_pow] at h
    exact (QuotientGroup.eq_one_iff _).mp h
  refine ‚ü®i + j, ?_‚ü©
  ext
  rw [SubgroupClass.coe_pow, OneMemClass.coe_one, ‚Üź hnx, ‚Üź map_pow]
  refine (QuotientGroup.eq_one_iff _).mpr (Subgroup.mem_inf.mpr ‚ü®?_, ?_‚ü©)
  ¬∑ rw [pow_add, pow_mul]
    exact Subgroup.pow_mem A hiA _
  ¬∑ rw [pow_add, mul_comm, pow_mul]
    exact Subgroup.pow_mem B hjB _

/-- **The trivial quotient is admissible**: all four clauses are trivial in a subsingleton.
(Nonvacuity of the admissible family, with no appeal to the Appendix-B `S‚āÉ` quotient.) -/
theorem isAdmissibleU_top :
    IsAdmissibleU (topOpenNormalSubgroup (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4))) := by
  haveI hsub : Subsingleton (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4) ‚ßł
      (topOpenNormalSubgroup (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4))).toSubgroup) :=
    QuotientGroup.subsingleton_quotient_top
  refine ‚ü®?_, Subsingleton.elim _ _, Subsingleton.elim _ _, fun g => ‚ü®0, Subtype.ext ?_‚ü©‚ü©
  ¬∑ rw [Marking.Generates, Subgroup.eq_top_iff']
    exact fun x => (Subsingleton.elim 1 x) ‚Ėł one_mem _
  ¬∑ exact Subsingleton.elim _ _

/-- Pushing a marking along a composite is composing the pushes. -/
@[simp] lemma Marking.map_map {G H K : Type*} [Group G] [Group H] [Group K]
    (f : G ‚Üí* H) (g : H ‚Üí* K) (t : Marking G) : (t.map f).map g = t.map (g.comp f) := rfl

/-- The wild pair of a pushed marking is the image of the wild pair. -/
private lemma image_wild_pair {H : Type*} [Group H] (f : FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4) ‚Üí* H) :
    ({(univMarking.map f).x‚āÄ, (univMarking.map f).x‚āĀ} : Set H)
      = f '' {univMarking.x‚āÄ, univMarking.x‚āĀ} := by
  rw [Set.image_pair]
  rfl

/-- **Admissibility is closed under intersections** (Lemma 2.1, subdirect closure): the
canonical quotient by `U ‚äď V` is a subdirect product of the quotients by `U` and by `V`, and
each admissibility clause passes through. -/
theorem isAdmissibleU_inf {U V : OpenNormalSubgroup (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4))}
    (hU : IsAdmissibleU U) (hV : IsAdmissibleU V) : IsAdmissibleU (U ‚äď V) := by
  refine ‚ü®generates_univMarking_map _, ?_, ?_, ?_‚ü©
  ¬∑ -- tame relation: the tame relator word lies in `U ‚äď V`
    exact (Marking.map_tameRelator_eq_one_iff (quotientMk (U ‚äď V).toSubgroup) univMarking).mp
      ((QuotientGroup.eq_one_iff _).mpr (Subgroup.mem_inf.mpr
        ‚ü®tameRelator_mem_of_isAdmissibleU hU, tameRelator_mem_of_isAdmissibleU hV‚ü©))
  ¬∑ -- wild relation: the wild relator word lies in `U ‚äď V`
    exact (Marking.map_wildRelator_eq_one_iff (quotientMk (U ‚äď V).toSubgroup) univMarking).mp
      ((QuotientGroup.eq_one_iff _).mpr (Subgroup.mem_inf.mpr
        ‚ü®wildRelator_mem_of_isAdmissibleU hU, wildRelator_mem_of_isAdmissibleU hV‚ü©))
  ¬∑ -- 2-core, subdirectly
    have hA := hU.2.2.2
    have hB := hV.2.2.2
    rw [Marking.Pro2Core, image_wild_pair] at hA hB
    rw [Marking.Pro2Core, image_wild_pair]
    exact isPGroup_normalClosure_image_inf {univMarking.x‚āÄ, univMarking.x‚āĀ}
      U.toSubgroup V.toSubgroup hA hB

/-- **Admissible domination.**  Every open normal subgroup of `F‚āĄ` containing `N_A` contains an
*admissible* open normal subgroup.  (Compactness: were every admissible `U ‚äĄ W`, the directed
family `{U ‚ą© WŠ∂ú}` of nonempty closed sets would have a common point, necessarily in
`N_A ‚ą© WŠ∂ú = ‚ąÖ`.) -/
theorem exists_isAdmissibleU_le {W : OpenNormalSubgroup (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4))}
    (hle : NA ‚Č§ W.toSubgroup) :
    ‚ąÉ U : OpenNormalSubgroup (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4)),
      IsAdmissibleU U ‚ąß U.toSubgroup ‚Č§ W.toSubgroup := by
  by_contra hcon
  replace hcon : ‚ąÄ U : OpenNormalSubgroup (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4)), IsAdmissibleU U ‚Üí
      ¬¨ U.toSubgroup ‚Č§ W.toSubgroup := fun U hU h => hcon ‚ü®U, hU, h‚ü©
  set őĻ := {U : OpenNormalSubgroup (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4)) // IsAdmissibleU U} with hőĻ
  haveI : Nonempty őĻ := ‚ü®‚ü®topOpenNormalSubgroup _, isAdmissibleU_top‚ü©‚ü©
  set t : őĻ ‚Üí Set (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4)) :=
    fun U => (U.1 : Set (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4))) ‚ą© (W.toSubgroup : Set _)Š∂ú with ht
  have htn : ‚ąÄ U, (t U).Nonempty :=
    fun U => SetLike.not_le_iff_exists.mp (hcon U.1 U.2)
  have htcl : ‚ąÄ U, IsClosed (t U) :=
    fun U => (U.1.toOpenSubgroup.isClosed).inter W.toOpenSubgroup.isOpen.isClosed_compl
  have htc : ‚ąÄ U, IsCompact (t U) := fun U => (htcl U).isCompact
  have htd : Directed (¬∑ ‚äá ¬∑) t := by
    intro U V
    exact ‚ü®‚ü®U.1 ‚äď V.1, isAdmissibleU_inf U.2 V.2‚ü©,
      Set.inter_subset_inter_left _ (SetLike.coe_subset_coe.mpr inf_le_left),
      Set.inter_subset_inter_left _ (SetLike.coe_subset_coe.mpr inf_le_right)‚ü©
  obtain ‚ü®x, hx‚ü© :=
    IsCompact.nonempty_iInter_of_directed_nonempty_isCompact_isClosed t htd htn htc htcl
  rw [Set.mem_iInter] at hx
  have hxNA : x ‚ąą NA := by
    rw [NA, Subgroup.mem_iInf]
    exact fun U => (hx U).1
  exact (hx (Classical.arbitrary őĻ)).2 (hle hxNA)

/-- Every open normal subgroup above `N_A` is itself admissible: push the marking forward from
a dominating admissible `U` along `F‚āĄ ‚ßł U ‚Ü† F‚āĄ ‚ßł W` (Lemma 2.2, `Marking.map_admissible`). -/
theorem isAdmissibleU_of_NA_le {W : OpenNormalSubgroup (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4))}
    (hle : NA ‚Č§ W.toSubgroup) : IsAdmissibleU W := by
  obtain ‚ü®U, hU, hUW‚ü© := exists_isAdmissibleU_le hle
  have hcomap : U.toSubgroup ‚Č§ Subgroup.comap (MonoidHom.id _) W.toSubgroup := by
    simpa using hUW
  set ŌÄ : (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4) ‚ßł U.toSubgroup) ‚Üí*
      (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4) ‚ßł W.toSubgroup) :=
    QuotientGroup.map U.toSubgroup W.toSubgroup (MonoidHom.id _) hcomap with hŌÄ
  have hŌÄs : Function.Surjective ŌÄ := by
    intro y
    obtain ‚ü®g, rfl‚ü© := QuotientGroup.mk'_surjective W.toSubgroup y
    refine ‚ü®QuotientGroup.mk' U.toSubgroup g, ?_‚ü©
    rw [hŌÄ, QuotientGroup.map_mk']
    rfl
  have hcomp : ŌÄ.comp (QuotientGroup.mk' U.toSubgroup) = QuotientGroup.mk' W.toSubgroup := by
    ext x
    rw [MonoidHom.comp_apply, hŌÄ, QuotientGroup.map_mk']
    rfl
  have hpush : univMarking.map (QuotientGroup.mk' W.toSubgroup)
      = (univMarking.map (QuotientGroup.mk' U.toSubgroup)).map ŌÄ := by
    rw [Marking.map_map, hcomp]
  rw [IsAdmissibleU, hpush]
  exact Marking.map_admissible ŌÄ hŌÄs _ hU

/-- **The admissible opens are exactly the opens above `N_A`** ‚ÄĒ the order-theoretic form of
"`őď_A = F‚āĄ ‚ßł N_A` is the largest quotient all of whose finite quotients are admissible"
(paper ¬ß2.1, eq. (7)).  This is the interface Prop 2.3 (P-05) consumes. -/
theorem isAdmissibleU_iff_NA_le (U : OpenNormalSubgroup (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4))) :
    IsAdmissibleU U ‚ÜĒ NA ‚Č§ U.toSubgroup :=
  ‚ü®fun h => iInf_le (fun V : {V : OpenNormalSubgroup (FreeProfiniteGroup (Fin 4)) //
      IsAdmissibleU V} => V.1.toSubgroup) ‚ü®U, h‚ü©, isAdmissibleU_of_NA_le‚ü©

end Directed

/-! ## The wild pair's closed normal closure is pro-2  (deliverable (ii))

The pro-2 clause of eq. (7) holds *in the limit*: the closed normal subgroup of `őď_A` generated
by the images of `x‚āÄ, x‚āĀ` is a pro-2 group.  Every open normal subgroup of it is trapped, via an
open normal subgroup of `őď_A`, by an admissible finite quotient of `F‚āĄ`, where the 2-core clause
of admissibility bounds every element by a 2-power. -/

section WildCore

/-- **The wild core of `őď_A`**: the closed normal closure `‚ü®‚ü®x‚āÄ, x‚āĀ‚ü©‚ü© ‚Č§ őď_A` of the images of
the wild generators ‚ÄĒ the subgroup that paper eq. (7) requires to be pro-2.  (Stated on the
underlying quotient `F‚āĄ ‚ßł N_A`, to which `GammaA` is definitionally equal.  The ¬ß3 layer's
`GQ2.SectionThree.wildPart` is *definitionally this subgroup* ‚ÄĒ deduplicated 2026-07-03 ‚ÄĒ
so `isProP_wildCore` etc. transfer verbatim; see `GQ2/SectionThree.lean`.) -/
